{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, the first person approach introduces the socio-demographic variables directly in the \"system\" prompt, a technique supposed to help confer a persona to the LLM; we do so using a first-person format (\"You are a 45 year old woman.",
    "You have a middle education level.",
    "\"), followed by a chat-format last question.",
    "We followed each strategy on the 140 US subpopulations, which amounts to nearly 2,800 unique prompts per question and per strategy.",
    "The results reveal some differences."
  ]
}